 below). Compare   Gaertner   and   Gardner  .","Slovenian: of German origin (see 1 above). In North America, this surname may also be an altered form of the Slovenized variant <b>Gartnar</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Gartler","meanings":["(2010: NA)","Austrian German: variant of   Gartner  .","German (<b>Gärtler</b>): rare variant of   Gertler  ."]},{"name":"Gaertner","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Franz, Helmut, Kurt, Dieter, Erna, Ernst, Gerhard, Hans, Irmgard, Karl Heinz, Ulrich.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic) (<b>Gärtner</b>): see   Gartner  ."]},{"name":"Gardner","meanings":["English and Scottish: occupational name from Middle English <i>gardener</i> ‘gardener’, Old French <i>gardinier</i>, <i>jardinier</i>.","Americanized form (translation into English) of German <b>Gärtner</b> or   Gartner   and French   Desjardins  ."]},{"name":"Gertner","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Alter, Chaim, Izidor, Mendel, Meyer, Shimon, Shmuel, Zalman.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of <b>Gärtner</b> ‘gardener’ (see   Gartner  )."]},{"name":"Gartmann","meanings":["German and Swiss German: occupational name for a gardener (see   Gartner  ); in some cases it may be a status name, referring to the owner of a small (enclosed or fenced) farm, or occupational name for a worker at a deer preserve (see   Garth  ). Compare   Gartman   and   Girtman  .","German: habitational name for someone from Garte near Osnabrück."]},{"name":"Gorder","meanings":["German (<b>Görder</b>): variant of <b>Gärtner</b> (see   Gartner  )."]}]},{"name":"Valten","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Valentin ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Valten Gärtner was born about 1464, in Großrückerswalde, Kreis Marienberg, Saxony, Germany. She had at least 2 sons with Valten Gärtner."},"et":{"um 1464–":"umbes 1464–Surnud","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1491–1564":"1491–